    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="429"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/518</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-18T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[For <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName>:]</p>
                <p>Your October 13, 5 p.m. Department would like to urge acceptance of plan at once
                    upon Japanese Ambassador here, but does not understand or see necessity for
                    phrase in Article 2, “who shall be appointed by the senior military officers of
                    the Allied forces in the several districts occupied by them.” Time presses for
                    early settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
